<Base title="Soft Smiths. Contemporary Women's* Metalwork — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>Soft Smiths. Contemporary Women's* Metalwork</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">Center of Polish Sculpture in Orońsko | 2025</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>The exhibition explores women artists reclaiming metalworking traditions. The curatorial concept frames this as symbolic resistance against "Swarog, the Slavic god of the sun, fire, and metallurgy," with participating artists emerging as "Swarożyce"—new goddesses with metallic manifestos.</p>
      <p>Eleven international women artists combine technical metalworking skills with critical reflection. Their work employs steel, aluminum, and lead to explore embodiment, ecology, mourning, care, violence, and relationships with non-human beings. The exhibition situates contemporary metalwork within broader "new materiality" trends.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Dates:</strong> July 5 – August 24, 2025</p>
      <p><strong>Curators:</strong> Michalina Sablik, Magdalena Lazar</p>
      <p><strong>Artists:</strong> Michalina Bigaj, Hannah Sophie Dunkelberg, Agata Ingarden, Lito Kattou, Magdalena Lazar, Lucia Leuci, Markéta Magidová, Ola Nenko, Emma Passera, Ala Savashevich, Weronika Wysocka</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-gallery" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
